# NOTE: Do NOT exclude .env / .env.* here. Vite reads them at build
# time inside the builder stage to bake VITE_* values (Clerk
# publishable key, AUTH_PROVIDER, etc.) into the static bundle.
# Multi-stage build still keeps the .env out of the runtime image
# because only /app/dist is copied to the nginx layer.
# Exclude .env.local-style files that should never ship though:
.env.development.local
.env.production.local
.env.test.local
